menu "breadboard: bb_mem_arena_tls"

config BB_MEM_ARENA_TLS_BYTES
    int "mbedTLS arena size (bytes; 0 = disabled, use heap fallback only)"
    range 0 65536
    default 0
    help
        Size in bytes of the static boot-reserved contiguous arena for mbedTLS
        allocations. When > 0 and CONFIG_MBEDTLS_CUSTOM_MEM_ALLOC=y, a
        static uint8_t buffer of this size backs a bb_mem_arena instance
        (components/bb_mem_arena) at boot. mbedTLS allocations are tried
        arena-first; if the arena is exhausted, the allocator falls back to
        the internal-heap facade (bb_calloc_internal() / bb_mem_free()).

        IMPORTANT: bb_mem_arena is a bump allocator — bb_mem_arena_free() does NOT
        reclaim space mid-handshake; freed bytes stay consumed until the
        arena is reset. bb_mem_arena_tls resets the arena automatically once
        every outstanding arena allocation has been freed (the arena fully
        drains between handshakes), so one arena is reused across many
        sequential handshakes over device uptime. Size this value for the
        CUMULATIVE allocation of ONE handshake (every allocation mbedTLS
        makes during that handshake, summed) — not just the peak
        concurrently-live bytes — because the bump pointer only rewinds on
        full drain, not on each individual free. If any allocation from a
        handshake is never freed, or the arena is exhausted mid-handshake,
        the outstanding count never reaches zero, the arena never resets,
        and subsequent allocations fall back to the internal heap until it
        does — a safe degradation, not a crash.

        0 (default) = no arena buffer; all mbedTLS allocations go directly to
        bb_calloc_internal() / bb_mem_free() (the ESP-IDF internal 8-bit pool).

        CONCURRENCY: the calloc/free hooks are the process-wide mbedTLS
        allocator and are guarded by a single mutex, so they are safe to call
        from multiple concurrent TLS handshakes (e.g. telemetry sink +
        OTA/update-check, WPA-supplicant). Concurrent callers are serialized,
        not parallelized — there is one shared arena, not one per caller.
        Size this value for the CUMULATIVE allocation across every handshake
        that may be concurrently in flight, not just a single handshake, and
        remember the arena reclaims (resets) only once ALL outstanding
        allocations across ALL callers have fully drained — a slow or stuck
        concurrent caller holding even one allocation blocks reclaim for
        everyone.

        Requires CONFIG_MBEDTLS_CUSTOM_MEM_ALLOC=y to have any effect.
        For no-PSRAM wroom32/c3/tdongle boards: set to 14336 (14 KB) to cover
        the manifest check TLS handshake's cumulative allocation (IN buffer +
        ssl_context + handshake).

endmenu
